==English==
===Etymology===
From Old French ''[[neveu]]'' (French ''[[neveu]]''), from {{L.}} ''[[nepos]]''

===Pronunciation===
*(''[[RP]]''): /nɛvju/, /<tt>nEvju</tt>/ (''somewhat dated'') ''or'' /nɛfju/, /<tt>nEfju</tt>/ 
*{{audio|en-us-nephew.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#a [[son]] of someone's [[brother]] ([[fraternal]] nephew)
#a son of someone's [[sister]] ([[sororal]] nephew)
#a son of someone's [[brother-in-law]]
#a son of someone's [[sister-in-law]]
#{{rfv-sense}} (''rare'') a [[lesbian]]

